<h2>3. Last blossom</h2>

<p>April is the time of the last blossom, both in the UK and Japan, where they have the cherry blossom (sakura) festival. It is a big tourist draw, occurring when the trees bloom from March to May (depending on their climate and location). I find the end of the blossom season, when the tress have all returned to their green, signals the end of Spring and the start of Summer. With longer, sunny days, between a blue sky and a green floor.</p>

